<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="74" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="1.[714,1247,169,792]" pageId="1" pageNumber="74">
ETYMOLOGY. — From the Greek 
<emphasis box="[1075,1147,170,194]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="74">pseudes</emphasis>
meaning false, and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1817" box="[821,938,195,219]" class="Malacostraca" family="Crangonidae" genus="Pontophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[821,938,195,219]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="74">Pontophilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a generic name proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="LEACH W. E." box="[714,847,221,245]" pageId="1" pageNumber="74" refId="ref6182" refString="LEACH W. E. 1817. - Malacostraca Podophthalma Britanniae; or Descriptions of the British Species of Crabs, Lobsters, Prawns, and of Other Malacostraca with Pedunculated Eyes. Part XV. Arding and Merret, London, 124 p., pls 22 B, 37 A." type="book" year="1817">Leach (1817)</bibRefCitation>
, and referring the superficial similarity of this new genus to the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1817" box="[990,1100,246,270]" class="Malacostraca" family="Crangonidae" genus="Pontophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[990,1100,246,270]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="74">Pontophilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="74" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[714,1247,169,792]" pageId="1" pageNumber="74">DIAGNOSIS. — Rostrum armed with one pair of lateral teeth. Carapace with postorbital suture; midline with more than two spines in anterior 0.60, but no spine on posterior 0.40; one additional spine superior to antennal spine; postorbital carina low, blunt, bearing three epibranchial spines. Anterior five abdominal somites devoid of median carinae; sixth somite without submedian carinae. Eye with cornea well developed, darkly pigmented. Antennular stylocerite not expanded laterally, terminating distally in acute spine. Scaphocerite with well developed blade. Maxilla with posterior lobe of scaphognathite rounded, not greatly elongate. First pereopod without exopod. Second pereopod chelate, short, but reaching distal end of merus of first pereopod; ischium and basis partially fused. Podobranch on second maxilliped; one arthrobranch above third maxilliped; pleurobranchs on fourth to eighth thoracic somites, each with anteriorly directed dorsal apex. Appendix masculina shorter and broader than appendix interna.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="76" pageId="1" pageNumber="74" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[714,1247,842,1669]" box="[714,814,842,868]" pageId="1" pageNumber="74">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[714,1247,842,1669]" lastBlockId="3.[151,684,170,709]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="76" pageId="1" pageNumber="74">
The new genus, which at present contains only the 
<typeStatus box="[758,805,906,932]" pageId="1" pageNumber="74">type</typeStatus>
species, is placed closest to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1817" box="[1122,1246,907,933]" class="Malacostraca" family="Crangonidae" genus="Pontophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1122,1246,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="74">Pontophilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Christoffersen" authorityYear="1988" box="[765,941,939,965]" class="Malacostraca" family="Crangonidae" genus="Parapontophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[765,941,939,965]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="74">Parapontophilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
using the key provided by 
<bibRefCitation author="HOLTHUIS L. B." box="[714,895,971,997]" pageId="1" pageNumber="74" refId="ref5981" refString="HOLTHUIS L. B. 1993. - The Recent Genera of the Caridean and Stenopodidean Shrimps (Crustacea, Decapoda) with an Appendix on the Order Amphionidacea. Nationaal Natuurhistorisch Museum, Leiden, 328 p." type="book" year="1993">Holthuis (1993)</bibRefCitation>
. The three genera share the rostrum armed with at least one pair of lateral teeth, shortened but chelate second pereopod, and the postorbital suture on the carapace. 
<taxonomicName authority="Komai, 2004" authorityName="Komai" authorityYear="2004" class="Malacostraca" family="Crangonidae" genus="Pseudopontophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="n. gen.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="74">Pseudopontophilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[786,863,1098,1124]" pageId="1" pageNumber="74" rank="genus">n. gen.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from both 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1817" box="[1073,1197,1099,1125]" class="Malacostraca" family="Crangonidae" genus="Pontophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1073,1197,1099,1125]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="74">Pontophilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Christoffersen" authorityYear="1988" box="[714,883,1131,1157]" class="Malacostraca" family="Crangonidae" genus="Parapontophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[714,883,1131,1157]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="74">Parapontophilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the completely loss of an exopod on the first pereopod and the more well developed second pereopod which reaches to the distal margin of the merus of the forwardly direct- ed first pereopod. The presence of more than two median spines in the anterior 0.70 on the carapace also characterizes 
<taxonomicName authority="Komai, 2004" authorityName="Komai" authorityYear="2004" box="[1038,1247,1323,1349]" class="Malacostraca" family="Crangonidae" genus="Pseudopontophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="n. gen.">
<emphasis box="[1038,1247,1323,1349]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="74">Pseudopontophilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[714,788,1354,1380]" pageId="1" pageNumber="74" rank="genus">n. gen.</taxonomicNameLabel>
In some characters, the new genus appears intermediate between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1817" box="[983,1118,1387,1413]" class="Malacostraca" family="Crangonidae" genus="Pontophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[983,1118,1387,1413]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="74">Pontophilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Christoffersen" authorityYear="1988" class="Malacostraca" family="Crangonidae" genus="Parapontophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="74">Parapontophilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In the general spination of the carapace (there are more than two median spines and more than one epibranchial spines), 
<taxonomicName authority="Komai, 2004" authorityName="Komai" authorityYear="2004" class="Malacostraca" family="Crangonidae" genus="Pseudopontophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="n. gen.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="74">Pseudopontophilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[857,940,1514,1540]" pageId="1" pageNumber="74" rank="genus">n. gen.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1817" box="[1103,1238,1515,1541]" class="Malacostraca" family="Crangonidae" genus="Pontophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1103,1238,1515,1541]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="74">Pontophilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, although no middorsal spine is present in the posterior half on the carapace in the new genus. While, the smooth abdomen lacking median or submedian carinae and the short, robust appendix masculina relate 
<taxonomicName authority="Komai, 2004" authorityName="Komai" authorityYear="2004" box="[351,558,171,197]" class="Malacostraca" family="Crangonidae" genus="Pseudopontophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="76" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="n. gen.">
<emphasis box="[351,558,171,197]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="76">Pseudopontophilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[569,651,170,196]" pageId="3" pageNumber="76" rank="genus">n. gen.</taxonomicNameLabel>
to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Christoffersen" authorityYear="1988" box="[151,320,203,229]" class="Malacostraca" family="Crangonidae" genus="Parapontophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="76" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,320,203,229]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="76">Parapontophilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5402895" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5402895" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5402895/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="75" startId="2.[152,163,1631,1648]" targetBox="[329,1079,194,1585]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph blockId="2.[152,1249,1631,1669]" pageId="2" pageNumber="75">
FIG. 1. — 
<taxonomicName authority="Komai, 2004" authorityName="Komai" authorityYear="2004" box="[231,462,1631,1648]" class="Malacostraca" family="Crangonidae" genus="Pseudopontophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serratus" status="n. gen., n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[231,462,1631,1648]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="75">Pseudopontophilus serratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[468,584,1631,1648]" pageId="2" pageNumber="75" rank="species">n. gen., n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, New Caledonia,SMIB 8, stn DW 148, holotype cl 5.6 mm (MNHN-Na 14186), habitus (lateral and dorsal views). Scale bar: 2 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,684,170,709]" pageId="3" pageNumber="76">
Further, 
<taxonomicName authority="Komai, 2004" authorityName="Komai" authorityYear="2004" box="[253,451,235,261]" class="Malacostraca" family="Crangonidae" genus="Pseudopontophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="76" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="n. gen.">
<emphasis box="[253,451,235,261]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="76">Pseudopontophilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[460,539,234,260]" pageId="3" pageNumber="76" rank="genus">n. gen.</taxonomicNameLabel>
superficially resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Stebbing, 1900" authorityName="Stebbing" authorityYear="1900" box="[266,565,267,293]" class="Malacostraca" family="Crangonidae" genus="Philocheras" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="76" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[266,385,267,293]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="76">Philocheras</emphasis>
Stebbing, 
<quantity box="[508,565,267,293]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.826" pageId="3" pageNumber="76" unit="in" value="1900.0">1900</quantity>
</taxonomicName>
in general appearance. The possession of the postorbital longitudinal suture on the carapace and the nontransversely oblong antennular stylocerite immediately distinguish the new genus from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stebbing" authorityYear="1900" class="Malacostraca" family="Crangonidae" genus="Philocheras" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="76" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="76">Philocheras</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The presence of a pair of lateral teeth on the rostrum is useful to separate 
<taxonomicName authority="Komai, 2004" authorityName="Komai" authorityYear="2004" class="Malacostraca" family="Crangonidae" genus="Pseudopontophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="76" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serratus" status="n. gen., n. sp.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="76">Pseudopontophilus serratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[304,451,490,516]" pageId="3" pageNumber="76" rank="species">n. gen., n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
from all but two species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stebbing" authorityYear="1900" box="[229,346,523,549]" class="Malacostraca" family="Crangonidae" genus="Philocheras" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="76" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[229,346,523,549]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="76">Philocheras</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Dardeau, 1980)" baseAuthorityName="Dardeau" baseAuthorityYear="1980" box="[362,635,522,549]" class="Malacostraca" family="Crangonidae" genus="Philocheras" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="76" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gorei">
<emphasis box="[362,442,522,547]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="76">P. gorei</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="DARDEAU M." box="[459,626,523,549]" pageId="3" pageNumber="76" pagination="563 - 572" refId="ref5878" refString="DARDEAU M. 1980. - A new species of Pontophilus (Crustacea: Natantia: Crangonidae) from the Gulf of Mexico and the western Atlantic. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington 93: 563 - 572." type="journal article" year="1980">Dardeau, 1980</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Wicksten, 1983" authorityName="Wicksten" authorityYear="1983" box="[151,462,554,581]" class="Malacostraca" family="Crangonidae" genus="Philocheras" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="76" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lapillus">
<emphasis box="[151,264,554,581]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="76">P. lapillus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="WICKSTEN M. K." box="[274,462,555,581]" pageId="3" pageNumber="76" pagination="78 - 83" refId="ref6631" refString="WICKSTEN M. K. 1983. - Synalpheus arostris and Philocheras lapillus, two new species of caridean shrimp (Crustacea) from the tropical eastern Pacific. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington 102: 78 - 83." type="journal article" year="1983">Wicksten, 1983</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, both of which are known to have lateral rostral teeth (
<bibRefCitation author="DARDEAU M." pageId="3" pageNumber="76" pagination="563 - 572" refId="ref5878" refString="DARDEAU M. 1980. - A new species of Pontophilus (Crustacea: Natantia: Crangonidae) from the Gulf of Mexico and the western Atlantic. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington 93: 563 - 572." type="journal article" year="1980">Dardeau 1980</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="WICKSTEN M. K." box="[222,392,619,645]" pageId="3" pageNumber="76" pagination="78 - 83" refId="ref6631" refString="WICKSTEN M. K. 1983. - Synalpheus arostris and Philocheras lapillus, two new species of caridean shrimp (Crustacea) from the tropical eastern Pacific. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington 102: 78 - 83." type="journal article" year="1983">Wicksten 1983</bibRefCitation>
). It is recommended to reassess the phylogenetic position of the latter two 
<taxonomicName box="[151,355,683,709]" class="Malacostraca" family="Crangonidae" genus="Philocheras" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="76" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[151,268,683,709]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="76">Philocheras</emphasis>
species.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
